Sibusiso Mpungose was sentenced to four life terms for the murder of his children. PIETERMARITZBURG - The KwaZulu-Natal High Court in Pietermaritzburg has sentenced Sibusiso Mpungose to four life terms for the murder of his children. The man's children aged 4, 6, and 10 were found hanged in their family home in early September. READ: Father accused of hanging four children now faces rape charge His 16-year-old stepdaughter was found strangled and the bush in Padfield Park in Pinetown. Mpungose pleaded guilty last month.